      "data": {
        "Name": "Drogon — Decision Gate 2 DG2 Concept Select",
        "Description": "DG2 Concept Select for the Drogon field development. Valysar fluvial formation across 7 reservoir segments (NorthSea, NorthHorst, CentralHorst, CentralFlanks, CentralSouth, SouthWing, EastLobe) with three facies types (Channel, Crevasse, Floodplain). Revised petrophysical interpretation: porosity reduced by factor 0.8 based on core analysis and thin sections. 50 FMU realisations quantify STOIIP uncertainty: P90 33.8 / P50 45.4 / P10 59.4 MSm³ oil in-place. Recoverable oil (P50) 14.8 MSm³ at 32.5% recovery factor. Recommended concept: subsea tie-back to FPSO with 2×4-slot templates, 12 production wells. NPV@10% 520 MUSD, CAPEX 8,500 MNOK, first oil 2028-H1.",
        "ProjectName": "Drogon Field Development",
        "DecisionLevelID": "dev:reference-data--DecisionLevel:DG2:1",
        "ApprovalStatusID": "dev:reference-data--DecisionApprovalStatus:Pending:1",
        "DecisionDueDate": "2026-06-30",
        "DecisionSummary": "Approve subsea tie-back development concept. Two 4-slot templates (8 slots), 12 wells targeting full 7-segment Valysar scope. Reference case STOIIP 45.4 MSm³ (P90 33.8, P10 59.4) — revised porosity interpretation ×0.8. Recoverable oil P50 14.8 MSm³ (RF 32.5%). First oil target 2028-H1. Proceed to DG3 FEED.",
        "RiskAssessmentDocument": "dev:work-product-component--Document:Drogon-SRA-DG2-Report:1",
